## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/armconstantpoolvalue">ARMConstantPoolValue</a> - <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/arm">ARM</a> specific constantpool value.

This is used to represent PC-relative displacement between the address of the load instruction and the constant being loaded, i.e. (&amp;GV-(LPIC+8)).

Definition at line 61 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/arm/armconstantpoolvalue-h">ARMConstantPoolValue.h</a>.
